					  ‌   ‌   ‌   ‌   ‌   ‌   ‌   ‌   ‌   ‌   ‌   ‌  Click here to see this online     Submit a Class Note  Update Your Information  Connect with Your College     Moving up Online  UIC's online bachelor's degree programs moved up to No. 3 in the 2020 U.S. News & World Report Best Online Programs rankings, and the program helps students move up, too. In its rankings, the publication notes that a bachelor's degree opens doors to employment opportunities and can lead to a higher salary for recipients. Read more .      Students register to vote on UIC's campus.  UIC Takes the Gold  When it comes to civic engagement, UIC students are among the best. During a ceremony held in Washington, D.C. last November, UIC received the ALL IN Campus Democracy Challenge's “Best Campus Action Plan” for 2018 and gold seal for having a campus voting rate between 40 and 49 percent in the 2018 midterm election. Read more .   Cynthia Soto, director of UIC's Native American Support Program, connected UIC researchers with Native American communities in Chicago.   Connecting with Indigenous Communities  Cynthia Soto BA ’97, MEd ’05 wants you to think about Native Americans—the engineers, lawyers, artists, teachers, students, neighbors and colleagues who live and work throughout Chicago, along with the historical tribes on whose land the city now sits. See how she helped bring indigenous communities together with UIC researchers. Read more.    Alumna Beth Gutelius researches the impact of automation on warehouse workers.  Replaced by Robots? Not So Fast  UIC alumna Beth Gutelius, MUPP '09, PhD '16, researches the impact of automation on warehouse workers, a hot topic that's generating national headlines. Gutelius was quoted in multiple publications and recently co-authored a published report on the topic that predicts: "The industry likely won’t experience dramatic job loss over the next decade, though many workers may see the content and quality of their jobs shift as technologies are adopted for particular tasks." Read more.   Golden Grads and 2019 graduates celebrated at UIC's December Commencement Ceremony.   Inspiring Graduates  UIC's alumni are smart, resilient and determined to make a difference. The December Commencement Ceremony celebrated the achievements of our newest alumni and our Golden Grads who returned to campus 50 years after their own graduation. Click here for the stories of three recent graduates who overcame any obstacles between them and their degrees. Click here to see photos of our 2019 Golden Grads.    Sami Alahmadi, UIC alumnus and 2020 Rhodes Scholar, represents Saudi Arabia.  UIC Alumnus Named Rhodes Scholar  Sami Alahmadi BS '18 has accomplished a rare feat. He is the second UIC-affiliated scholar to be selected for the Rhodes Scholarship, one of the most prestigious international scholarship programs. It enables outstanding students from around the world who demonstrate high potential in learning and leading to study at the University of Oxford. Alahmadi represents the Saudi Arabia constituency. Rudyard Sadleir, a UIC Honors College senior majoring in environmental geology, was chosen from the U.S. constituency in 2000. Read more .    Nominate Outstanding Alumni for UICAA Awards  Each year, the UIC Alumni Association celebrates outstanding alumni in a variety of fields with the highest alumni honors presented by the university, the UIC Alumni Awards. If you know an alumna/us who is an inspiration to the UIC community, we want to know. Complete the award nomination form here  by March 31.     UIC alumni and students enjoyed games at a social in Des Plaines.   Alumni & Student Social in Des Plaines  Food, drink and camaraderie filled the room as UIC alumni and students met at the Tap House Grill in Des Plaines on November 7, 2019, to network and connect in the community where they live. Attendees were treated to the Handshake Huddle, an exercise on giving the perfect handshake in a professional setting, a trivia competition with prizes and board games. For more photos, click here .    More than 600 graduating students visited Grad Fest at the end of fall semester.  Grad Fest  More than 600 graduating students visited this year’s Grad Fest on UIC's campus to recognize the culmination of their hard work and perseverance. Graduates picked up regalia, learned about alumni services and celebrated their accomplishments with their classmates. To see more photos, click here .      DATE  EVENT HOST  EVENT  CONTACT    February 5  College of Nursing  Springfield Alumni Social  RSVP    February 8  UIC Alumni Association  Alumni Reception & Men's Basketball Game  RSVP     February 15  College of Engineering  Motor Row & Auto Show  RSVP     February 21   College of Dentistry   CDS Midwinter Reception   Info     February 28  College of Nursing  Urbana Alumni & Friends Event  RSVP    March 4  UIC Alumni Association  UIC's Response to the Opioid Epidemic Alumni Networking Reception  RSVP    March 5  College of Dentistry  33rd Annual Clinic & Research Day    RSVP    March 12  College of Pharmacy  Cubs vs. Dodgers in Mesa, Arizona  RSVP    March 13  College of Applied Health Sciences  OT Scholarship of Practice Day  Save the Date    March 18  College of Nursing  Chicago Alumni & Student Social  RSVP    March 21  College of Pharmacy  Alumni Reception at APhA Annual Meeting  RSVP    April 1  Office of the Vice Chancellor for Research  UIC Research and Impact Day  Save the Date    April 2  School of Public Health  Annual Alumni Celebration  RSVP    April 2  College of Applied Health Sciences  2020 AHS Celebrates  Save the Date    April 17  College of Dentistry  CE Course: Ted Weclew Lecture  Info    April 24  College of Dentistry  Alumni Reunion  Save the Date        Update Your Information    Submit a Class Note    Connect to Your College      Stay Connected!      University of Illinois at Chicago UIC Alumni Association 750 S. Halsted St. 312-413-8272 uicalumni@uic.edu  Unsubscribe from UIC Alumni Associati